<dl id="n12112d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12112d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12112d"> 112(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> la r&egrave;gle de Bangor est bonne</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo; <mark>La r&egrave;gle de Bangor est bonne</mark>, disait une vieille s&eacute;quence; elle est droite, divine, aust&egrave;re, sainte et exacte, souverainement juste et digne d&apos;admiration. <br><font color="green">[&ldquo;The rule of Bangor is good&rdquo;, said an old hymn, &ldquo;it is upright, divine, austere, holy, rigorous, supremely just and worthy of admiration&rdquo;]</font> <small> <a name="STCM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#STCM"><cite title="source">Saint Colomban</cite></a> (1905) 5</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
